<span id="freeTextContainer12158714684467916851">Even though I like both Hitchens and Orwell I couldn&apos;t get into this at all. It seemed written for the academic-philosopher type. A lot of name-dropping of what other people said or thought of Orwell. A lot of meandering. Not much said on Orwell&apos;s thoughts, personality, and life. <br/><br/>One chapter is titled &quot;Orwell and the Feminists: Difficulties with Girls&quot;. Girls! Come on Christopher - get in the 20th century (this was written in 2002).<br/><br/>Maybe if you read a lot on Orwell this could appeal to you - may</span>
