        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3434629991" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16685911579476865086">While this is certainly loose and somewhat messy, I have to rate it highly for being so entertaining — and entertaining in spite of making reference to many debates and ideas of which I was hitherto unaware. The book is written with a journalistic flare, and exudes Hitchens&apos; carefully-crafted polemical, contrarian style; in keeping with this, it sometimes comes across as a mere series of tasty take-downs of Orwell&apos;s detractors. Yet, the book is able to rise above this; it is, in the end, a great</span>
  <span id="freeText16685911579476865086" style="display:none">While this is certainly loose and somewhat messy, I have to rate it highly for being so entertaining — and entertaining in spite of making reference to many debates and ideas of which I was hitherto unaware. The book is written with a journalistic flare, and exudes Hitchens' carefully-crafted polemical, contrarian style; in keeping with this, it sometimes comes across as a mere series of tasty take-downs of Orwell's detractors. Yet, the book is able to rise above this; it is, in the end, a great call for individual intellectual integrity in the face of dogmatic factionalism.</span>
