  <span id="freeText4841327239666890222" style="display:none">Hitchens is such a better writer when he's investigating personalities than trying to take on generalities. His takedowns of Kissinger and Mother Teresa were wonderful, and when he's examining Orwell, he shies away from hagiography, and points out that Orwell, while a great writer and a great man, is not the secular saint he's so often painted as. A humane and broad-ranging analysis of a fascinating figure, warts and all.</span>
